        "body": "Fixes #281218\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nWhen an MCP server definition provider updates the version field (e.g., from 0.1 to 0.2), users had to manually click 'Update Tools' to refresh the tool list. This was not intuitive and interrupted the workflow.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nThis PR implements automatic tool updates when the server definition version changes. The system now:\r\n- Monitors the cache state for `Outdated` status\r\n- Detects when the definition version (cacheNonce) changes\r\n- Automatically triggers a server restart to fetch updated tools\r\n- Performs the update silently without user interaction\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n- Added `_lastAutoUpdatedNonce` property to `McpServer` class to track the last auto-updated version and prevent infinite update loops\r\n- Added an `autorun` effect that monitors `cacheState` for `Outdated` status\r\n- When an outdated state is detected with a new version, automatically triggers server restart\r\n- Uses silent update (`promptType: 'never'`, `errorOnUserInteraction: true`) to avoid interrupting user workflow\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n- Changed the version in `McpServerDefinitionProvider` from 0.1 to 0.2\r\n- Verified that tools are automatically updated without manual intervention\r\n- Confirmed no infinite update loops occurFixes #281218\r\n\r\nWhen an MCP server definition provider updates the version field (e.g., from 0.1 to 0.2), VS Code now automatically detects the change and refreshes the tools without requiring manual 'Update Tools' clicks.\r\n\r\nChanges:\r\n- Added _lastAutoUpdatedNonce property to McpServer to track the last auto-updated version and prevent infinite update loops\r\n- Added autorun effect that monitors cacheState for Outdated status\r\n- When outdated state is detected with a new version, automatically triggers server restart to fetch updated tools\r\n- Uses silent update (promptType: 'never', errorOnUserInteraction: true) to avoid interrupting the user workflow\r\n\r\n<!-- Thank you for submitting a Pull Request. Please:\r\n* Read our Pull Request guidelines:\r\n  https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/wiki/How-to-Contribute#pull-requests\r\n* Associate an issue with the Pull Request.\r\n* Ensure that the code is up-to-date with the `main` branch.\r\n* Include a description of the proposed changes and how to test them.\r\n-->\r\n",
